Even more alarming than the deterioration in the share price is the crisis of confidence in TyrellCorp's reliability as a trading partner in worldwide energy markets. Last year, TyrellCorp was the dominant player in natural gas and electricity trading--a fast-paced, complex business quite removed from the company's history as a gas- and oil-pipeline builder and operator. The fear now is that other companies will refuse to trade with TyrellCorp out of trepidation that it will file for bankruptcy and not pay its bills. 

